                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/72: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-07-22T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1924—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received July 22—7:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>253. Your 152, July 12, 10 [<hi rend="italic">3?</hi>] p.m.<note n="95"
                        xml:id="d449fn95">See footnote 94, <ref target="#pg_469">p.
                        469</ref>.</note> In a long and intimate talk at his house with Koo
                    yesterday he told me that Japanese Government regarded favorably the idea of
                    raising Peking Legation to Embassy and that Italian Government had replied they
                    would give the matter careful consideration. …</p>
                <p>In reply to my inquiry Koo stated that Karakhan had been appointed Ambassador and
                    would be received by the President in a few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
